# =============================================================================
# GitHub Actions Variables Checklist
# =============================================================================
# Configure these in: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables
# NO SECRETS ARE REQUIRED AT ALL (Password is stored securely in GCP)
# =============================================================================

# REQUIRED VARIABLES:
# ☐ GCP_PROJECT_ID
#    Your GCP project ID (e.g., "my-project-123456")

# ☐ BIGQUERY_DATASET
#    BigQuery dataset name (default: "copo_do_mundo")

# ☐ BIGQUERY_TABLE
#    BigQuery table name (default: "votes")

# ☐ CLOUD_STORAGE_BUCKET
#    Cloud Storage bucket name (e.g., "my-project-copo-do-mundo-images")
#    Must be globally unique

# ☐ WIF_PROVIDER
#    Workload Identity Provider string (printed at the end of infra/gcp-setup.sh)

# ☐ WIF_SERVICE_ACCOUNT
#    Service account email for deployment (printed at the end of infra/gcp-setup.sh)

# ☐ CLOUD_RUN_SERVICE_ACCOUNT
#    Service account email for Cloud Run (same as WIF_SERVICE_ACCOUNT)

# =============================================================================
# Quick Setup:
# 1. Run: ./infra/gcp-setup.sh (creates GCP resources AND variables)
# 2. Add all variables above in GitHub Variables section
# 3. Open GCP Console -> Security -> Secret Manager -> Update 'admin-password'
# 4. Push to main branch to trigger deployment
# =============================================================================
